### Generation Logic

#### [NEW] [prompts.py](file:///c:/HelioX/composer/prompts.py)

- `COMPOSER_SYSTEM_PROMPT`: Strict rules enforcing exactly the JSON schema, that every factual claim must append `[C1]`, `[C2]` etc., and that constraints must be explicitly stated.
- `build_composer_prompt`: Formats the Adjudicated Result claims (with auto-assigned Cx IDs) and SQO into the user payload.

#### [NEW] [generator.py](file:///c:/HelioX/composer/generator.py)

- `AnswerComposer.generate(sqo, adjudication_result)`:
  1. Checks `global_coverage_score < 0.60`. If true, bypass LLM and return static `"Insufficient evidence to fully answer this query."` with partial results.
  2. Assigns sequential IDs (`[C1]`, `[C2]`) to the `selected_claims`.
  3. Calls LLM (Gemini API / mockable) with `response_format={"type": "json_object"}`.
  4. Parses the JSON into `FinalAnswer`.
  5. Populates constraints applied block and confidence/coverage from input metadata.

